      "date": "2015-05-01 16:13:14.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: Code-Review-1\n\nThis change cannot be cherry-picked to master.\nPlease rebase the change locally and upload the rebased commit for review.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "222a17fdcaa42109266651093afd5f9c31189f0e",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 109,
        "name": "Christopher J. Morrone",
        "email": "morrone2@llnl.gov",
        "username": "morrone"
      },
      "date": "2015-06-02 22:05:18.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: Code-Review-1\n\nI do not think this is the correct approach.  This means that by default the packaging for the client modules that are built during a full build of lustre will be different from the packages for the client modules that are built during the serverless build.  That kind of inconsistency is just really darn confusing.\n\nI think we would be better off going all the way and correctly kmod packing the lustre modules all the time.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
