        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Alexander.Boyko",
          "email": "alexander_boyko@xyratex.com",
          "date": "2015-04-23 08:10:33.000000000",
          "tz": 180
        },
        "subject": "LU-5614 build: add kmod for client",
        "message": "LU-5614 build: add kmod for client\n\nWhen the Lustre is built as client with driver update support,\nkmod package has ability to check and copy modules for the new\nadded kernel. The package includes dependencies on a kernel symbols\nversion. In most cases this is enough for a minor security kernel\nupdates. New param build_kmod was added to spec file. For Lustre\nclient build_kmod is enabled by default, and disabled for servers.\n\nThis patch changes the Lustre modules location to\n[extra|updates]/lustre-client/[fs|net]/ for client build.\nKmod utils/scripts requires this modification, cause they use %name\nfor postinstall scripts. Path to Lustre modules for server build\nstay the same.\n\nSigned-off-by: Alexander Boyko <alexander.boyko@seagate.com>\nXyratex-bug-id: MRP-1759\nChange-Id: I159c2d29577a605c0c96e0c9d93a86e7518b28fb\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
